---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
---

<Layout title="For Developers">
  <body class="h-screen flex flex-col">
    <Header active="developers" />
    <main class="relative w-full">
      <!-- Right: tree image scoped to main content only -->
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 right-0 w-[45%] pointer-events-none overflow-hidden">
        <img src="/sidetrees.jpg" class="w-full h-full object-cover" style="filter: grayscale(100%);" alt="" />
        <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background-color: #098727; mix-blend-mode: screen; opacity: 0.5;"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #f4f4f4 0%, transparent 60%), linear-gradient(to bottom, #f4f4f4 0%, transparent 15%);"></div>
      </div>
      <!-- Left: all text content -->
      <div class="relative flex flex-col gap-16 py-16 pl-16 pr-8 w-[55%]">
        <div class="prose mt-8 mb-16 w-[60vw] max-w-none">
          <h1 class="whitespace-nowrap">Usher in a new era of the web.</h1>
          <h3>
            If you believe, like us, that the status quo is broken, then join us in building a better web. The web didn't become the way it is now because
            it's the only way-it's because money and infrastructure was poured
            into making it so. We can redirect this energy towards building an internet
            that doesn't require software companies to prey on users to survive.
            After all, it's just code.
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="prose mb-16">
          <h2>
            Aligned incentives: you own the product, the user owns their data.
          </h2>
          <p>
            We believe software is at its best when company business models align
            with user incentives. Users should pay you because they want to stay,
            not because they can't leave.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="prose mb-16">
          <h2>No infrastructure necessary.</h2>
          <p>
            Today, every company has to rebuild some of the same infrastructure:
            user accounts, permissions, data sync. We get these primitives right
            so you can focus on what matters most: building the best user
            experience. Save the time, money, and compute by building on habitat.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="prose mb-16">
          <h2>Trivial integration with other apps built on ATProtocol.</h2>
          <p>
            The benefit of an open data protocol is that products thrive together.
            You don't just read and write to your application's data silo;
            instead, shared data schemas allow for unlimited integration and
            cross-app interactions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <footer class="flex justify-center py-16 px-8">
      <div class="prose w-[90vw] max-w-none text-center">
        <h3 class="text-center">
          Get started by reading our docs or join the discussion on your favorite platform by tagging <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/habitat.network">@habitat.network</a>.
        </h3>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</Layout>
